      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none dark:prose-invert">

          <!-- Important Notice -->
          <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 border border-red-200 dark:border-red-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="mt-0 text-red-900 dark:text-red-100">Important Legal Requirements</h2>
            <p class="mb-0">
              <strong>ANPR technology processes vehicle data that may be subject to privacy laws and regulations.</strong> 
              By using MicroANPR services, you acknowledge that you are responsible for ensuring your use complies 
              with all applicable laws, regulations, and ethical standards in your jurisdiction.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2>1. Scope and Application</h2>
          
          <h3>1.1 Purpose</h3>
          <p>
            These Terms of Use define acceptable and prohibited uses of MicroANPR's Automatic Number Plate 
            Recognition (ANPR) services. These terms supplement our 
            <a href="/terms" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Terms of Service</a> 
            and must be read together with that agreement.
          </p>

          <h3>1.2 Who Must Comply</h3>
          <p>These terms apply to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>All users of MicroANPR services</li>
            <li>Organizations using our services on behalf of others</li>
            <li>Third parties accessing our services through customer integrations</li>
            <li>Anyone processing data obtained through our services</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>2. Lawful and Ethical Use</h2>

          <h3>2.1 Legal Compliance</h3>
          <p>You must ensure your use of ANPR services complies with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Data Protection Laws:</strong> UK GDPR, Data Protection Act 2018, and local privacy laws</li>
            <li><strong>Surveillance Regulations:</strong> CCTV codes of practice and surveillance legislation</li>
            <li><strong>Human Rights Laws:</strong> Right to privacy and freedom of movement</li>
            <li><strong>Industry Regulations:</strong> Sector-specific compliance requirements</li>
            <li><strong>Local Laws:</strong> All applicable national, regional, and local legislation</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.2 Lawful Basis Requirements</h3>
          <p>Before using ANPR services, you must establish a proper lawful basis:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Explicit consent from data subjects where required</li>
            <li><strong>Contract:</strong> Processing necessary for contract performance</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> Compliance with legal requirements</li>
            <li><strong>Legitimate Interest:</strong> Balanced against individual rights and freedoms</li>
            <li><strong>Public Task:</strong> Exercise of official authority or public interest</li>
            <li><strong>Vital Interests:</strong> Protection of life or physical safety</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. Permitted Use Cases</h2>

          <h3>3.1 Traffic Management</h3>
          <p>Acceptable traffic management applications include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Congestion Monitoring:</strong> Analyzing traffic patterns and flow</li>
            <li><strong>Journey Time Measurement:</strong> Calculating travel times between points</li>
            <li><strong>Traffic Enforcement:</strong> Speed cameras and traffic violation detection (with proper authorization)</li>
            <li><strong>Road Usage Analytics:</strong> Understanding road utilization patterns</li>
            <li><strong>Incident Detection:</strong> Identifying traffic incidents and emergencies</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.2 Security and Access Control</h3>
          <p>Legitimate security applications include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Facility Access:</strong> Controlling entry to private properties and facilities</li>
            <li><strong>Perimeter Security:</strong> Monitoring facility boundaries and restricted areas</li>
            <li><strong>Asset Protection:</strong> Securing valuable assets and infrastructure</li>
            <li><strong>Emergency Response:</strong> Supporting security and emergency services</li>
            <li><strong>Workplace Safety:</strong> Ensuring authorized vehicle access only</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.3 Parking Management</h3>
          <p>Approved parking applications include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Payment Enforcement:</strong> Ensuring parking fees are paid</li>
            <li><strong>Time Limit Enforcement:</strong> Managing parking duration limits</li>
            <li><strong>Permit Validation:</strong> Verifying parking permits and authorization</li>
            <li><strong>Space Optimization:</strong> Analyzing parking utilization</li>
            <li><strong>Customer Service:</strong> Improving parking experience</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3.4 Law Enforcement</h3>
          <p>Law enforcement use requires proper authorization and includes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Crime Prevention:</strong> Deterring criminal activity (with appropriate legal authority)</li>
            <li><strong>Investigation Support:</strong> Assisting in criminal investigations</li>
            <li><strong>Missing Vehicle Recovery:</strong> Locating stolen or missing vehicles</li>
            <li><strong>Public Safety:</strong> Supporting public safety initiatives</li>
            <li><strong>Border Control:</strong> Supporting authorized border security operations</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Prohibited Uses</h2>

          <h3>4.1 Illegal Activities</h3>
          <p>You may not use our services for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Unauthorized Surveillance:</strong> Monitoring without legal basis or proper consent</li>
            <li><strong>Stalking or Harassment:</strong> Tracking individuals without authorization</li>
            <li><strong>Discrimination:</strong> Using vehicle data for discriminatory purposes</li>
            <li><strong>Privacy Violations:</strong> Infringing on reasonable expectations of privacy</li>
            <li><strong>Data Theft:</strong> Unauthorized collection or use of personal data</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>4.2 Misuse of Technology</h3>
          <p>Prohibited technical uses include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>System Attacks:</strong> Attempting to hack, disrupt, or compromise our services</li>
            <li><strong>Reverse Engineering:</strong> Attempting to extract our algorithms or technology</li>
            <li><strong>Data Mining:</strong> Extracting data for unauthorized commercial purposes</li>
            <li><strong>Service Abuse:</strong> Using services in ways that degrade performance for others</li>
            <li><strong>False Data:</strong> Submitting fake or manipulated images</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>4.3 Unethical Applications</h3>
          <p>We prohibit use for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Mass Surveillance:</strong> Indiscriminate monitoring of public spaces without proper authorization</li>
            <li><strong>Political Monitoring:</strong> Tracking individuals based on political activities or beliefs</li>
            <li><strong>Social Credit Systems:</strong> Creating systems to score or rank individuals</li>
            <li><strong>Biometric Profiling:</strong> Attempting to extract biometric data from vehicle occupants</li>
            <li><strong>Predictive Policing:</strong> Using ANPR for predictive law enforcement without proper safeguards</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. Data Responsibility</h2>

          <h3>5.1 Data Controller Obligations</h3>
          <p>As a data controller, you must:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Privacy Notices:</strong> Provide clear privacy notices to data subjects</li>
            <li><strong>Data Minimization:</strong> Process only necessary data for your stated purpose</li>
            <li><strong>Retention Limits:</strong> Delete data when no longer needed</li>
            <li><strong>Security Measures:</strong> Implement appropriate data security</li>
            <li><strong>Individual Rights:</strong> Respond to data subject rights requests</li>
            <li><strong>Impact Assessments:</strong> Conduct DPIAs for high-risk processing</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>5.2 Transparency Requirements</h3>
          <p>You must provide clear information about:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>ANPR Operations:</strong> Clearly indicate when ANPR is in use</li>
            <li><strong>Data Processing:</strong> Explain what data is collected and why</li>
            <li><strong>Retention Periods:</strong> Specify how long data will be kept</li>
            <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Provide contact details for data protection queries</li>
            <li><strong>Rights Information:</strong> Explain individual rights and how to exercise them</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>6. Geographic and Jurisdictional Considerations</h2>

          <h3>6.1 Cross-Border Data Processing</h3>
          <p>When processing data across borders, ensure:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Transfer Legality:</strong> Data transfers comply with applicable laws</li>
            <li><strong>Adequacy Decisions:</strong> Utilize approved transfer mechanisms</li>
            <li><strong>Safeguarding Measures:</strong> Implement appropriate safeguards</li>
            <li><strong>Local Compliance:</strong> Comply with laws in all processing locations</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>6.2 Public Space Considerations</h3>
          <p>For public space ANPR deployment:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Proportionality:</strong> Ensure measures are proportionate to the objective</li>
            <li><strong>Necessity:</strong> Demonstrate that ANPR is necessary for the purpose</li>
            <li><strong>Public Interest:</strong> Establish legitimate public interest</li>
            <li><strong>Alternative Measures:</strong> Consider less intrusive alternatives</li>
            <li><strong>Regular Review:</strong> Periodically review necessity and proportionality</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>7. Technical and Operational Requirements</h2>

          <h3>7.1 Data Quality and Accuracy</h3>
          <p>You are responsible for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Image Quality:</strong> Providing clear, high-quality source images</li>
            <li><strong>Camera Positioning:</strong> Proper camera setup for accurate recognition</li>
            <li><strong>Data Validation:</strong> Verifying accuracy of processed results</li>
            <li><strong>Error Correction:</strong> Implementing processes to handle recognition errors</li>
            <li><strong>Quality Monitoring:</strong> Regular assessment of system performance</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>7.2 System Integration</h3>
          <p>Integration requirements include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Security Standards:</strong> Implementing appropriate API security</li>
            <li><strong>Error Handling:</strong> Proper handling of service errors and failures</li>
            <li><strong>Rate Limiting:</strong> Respecting API rate limits and usage policies</li>
            <li><strong>Data Synchronization:</strong> Ensuring data consistency across systems</li>
            <li><strong>Audit Logging:</strong> Maintaining logs of system interactions</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>8. Monitoring and Enforcement</h2>

          <h3>8.1 Usage Monitoring</h3>
          <p>We monitor service usage to detect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Policy Violations:</strong> Uses that violate these terms</li>
            <li><strong>Suspicious Patterns:</strong> Unusual usage patterns that may indicate misuse</li>
            <li><strong>Technical Issues:</strong> Performance problems or system abuse</li>
            <li><strong>Compliance Issues:</strong> Potential legal or regulatory violations</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>8.2 Enforcement Actions</h3>
          <p>Violations may result in:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Warnings:</strong> Formal notice of policy violations</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Restrictions:</strong> Limitations on service access or features</li>
            <li><strong>Service Suspension:</strong> Temporary suspension of service access</li>
            <li><strong>Account Termination:</strong> Permanent termination for serious violations</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Action:</strong> Referral to law enforcement for illegal activities</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>9. Reporting and Support</h2>

          <h3>9.1 Violation Reporting</h3>
          <p>Report suspected violations to:</p>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4">
            <ul class="mb-0">
              <li><strong>Info:</strong> info@microanpr.com</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3>9.2 Compliance Assistance</h3>
          <p>We provide support for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Technical Support:</strong> Assistance with proper implementation</li>
            <li><strong>Best Practices:</strong> Recommendations for responsible use</li>
            <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Compliance documentation and certifications</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>10. Updates and Changes</h2>

          <h3>10.1 Policy Updates</h3>
          <p>We may update these Terms of Use to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Legal Changes:</strong> Reflect changes in applicable laws</li>
            <li><strong>Technology Evolution:</strong> Address new technologies or capabilities</li>
            <li><strong>Best Practices:</strong> Incorporate industry best practices</li>
            <li><strong>Clarification:</strong> Provide clearer guidance on acceptable use</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>10.2 Notification Process</h3>
          <p>Changes will be communicated through:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Email Notification:</strong> Direct notification to account holders</li>
            <li><strong>Dashboard Alerts:</strong> Prominent notices in your account dashboard</li>
            <li><strong>Website Updates:</strong> Updates to this terms page</li>
            <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Updates to compliance documentation</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>11. Contact and Resources</h2>

          <h3>11.1 Contact Information</h3>
          <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 rounded-lg p-6">
            <p><strong>For questions about these Terms of Use:</strong></p>
            <ul class="mb-4">
              <li><strong>Contact:</strong> info@microanpr.com</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3>11.2 Additional Resources</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/terms" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Terms of Service</a> - Full service agreement</li>
            <li><a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a> - How we handle your data</li>
            <li><a href="/security" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Security</a> - Our security measures and practices</li>
            <li><a href="/privacy" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Cookie Policy</a> - Our use of cookies</li>
          </ul>



        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>
